<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1314&amp;p=11468#p11468"><![CDATA[
The assembler I use most often (ca65) accepts at least 'asl a', and this appears to be the official syntax, but the Apple mini-assembler used 'asl'. I'd recommend following <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jon_Postel" class="postlink">Postel's law</a> by accepting both syntaxes; it won't hurt anything.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Apr 01, 2006 7:45 pm</p><hr />
