<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1314&amp;p=11465#p11465"><![CDATA[
A robust assembler should accept both 'asl' and 'asl a' and assemble them to the same opcode. A particular assembler might accept one or the other; read its documentation. Which assembler are you working with?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Apr 01, 2006 7:14 pm</p><hr />
